defs.docs:
This library provides a way to access system information such as CPU load, mounted filesystems,
 network interfaces, etc.

defs.name: platform
defs.docs: This module reexports the OS-specific module that actually implements Platform.

defs.name: Platform
defs.docs: The Platform trait declares all the functions for getting system information.

defs.name: cpu_load
defs.docs: Returns a delayed vector of CPU load statistics, one object per CPU (core).

defs.name: cpu_load_aggregate
defs.docs: Returns a delayed CPU load statistics object, average over all CPUs (cores).

defs.name: load_average
defs.docs: Returns a load average object.

defs.name: memory
defs.docs: Returns a memory information object.

defs.name: uptime
defs.docs: Returns the system uptime.

defs.name: boot_time
defs.docs: Returns the system boot time.

defs.name: battery_life
defs.docs: Returns a battery life information object.

defs.name: on_ac_power
defs.docs: Returns whether AC power is plugged in.

defs.name: mounts
defs.docs: Returns a vector of filesystem mount information objects.

defs.name: mount_at
defs.docs: Returns a filesystem mount information object for the filesystem at a given path.

defs.name: block_device_statistics
defs.docs: Returns a map of block device statistics objects

defs.name: networks
defs.docs: Returns a map of network intefrace information objects.

defs.name: network_stats
defs.docs: Returns statistics for a given interface (bytes/packets sent/received)

defs.name: cpu_temp
defs.docs: Returns the current CPU temperature in degrees Celsius.

defs.name: socket_stats
defs.docs: Returns information about the number of sockets in use

defs.name: data
defs.docs: This module provides the data structures that represent system information.

defs.name: DelayedMeasurement
defs.docs: A wrapper for a measurement that takes time.

defs.name: CPULoad
defs.value: CPULoad { user, nice, system, interrupt, idle, platform }

defs.name: CpuTime
defs.value: CpuTime { user, nice, system, interrupt, idle, other }

defs.name: Filesystem
defs.value: Filesystem { files, files_total, files_avail, free, avail, total, name_max, fs_type, fs_mounted_from, fs_mounted_on }

defs.name: BlockDeviceStats
defs.value: BlockDeviceStats { name, read_ios, read_merges, read_sectors, read_ticks, write_ios, write_merges, write_sectors, write_ticks, in_flight, io_ticks, time_in_queue }

defs.name: NetworkStats
defs.value: NetworkStats { rx_bytes, tx_bytes, rx_packets, tx_packets, rx_errors, tx_errors }

defs.name: SocketStats
defs.value: SocketStats { tcp_sockets_in_use, tcp_sockets_orphaned, udp_sockets_in_use, tcp6_sockets_in_use, udp6_sockets_in_use }
